p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 =
1em 0;">Once they&#8217;ve built those network effects, though, and they kn=
ow that users, developers, and businesses are locked in, they switch from &=
#8220;attract&#8221; to &#8220;extract.&#8221; The easiest way to grow reve=
nue is to start charging businesses and developers to reach customers, and =
to serve customers ads or products based on the data they&#8217;ve accumula=
ted.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">To be clear, I don&#8217;t think there&#8217;s anyth=
ing inherently evil in this. I could leave Twitter if I felt that I was get=
ting screwed, and indeed, many people deleted Facebook after the Cambridge =
Analytica scandal and after many incidents since then.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D=
"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">It=
&#8217;s a market. The way the internet is currently architected allows for=
 companies to capture value, and they do.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a=
1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Web3, then, isn=
&#8217;t as much an idealistic repudiation of Web 2.0 (although that&#8217;=
s a good marketing tool) as much as it is a natural evolution of the market=
 made possible by new technology.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Web3 is the next versio=
n of the internet, built on top of crypto-economic networks, like Bitcoin a=
nd Ethereum. According to Dixon, &#8220;Cryptonetworks combine the best fea=
tures of the first two internet eras: <strong>community-governed, decentral=
ized networks</strong> with <strong>capabilities that will eventually excee=
d those of the most advanced centralized services</strong>.&#8221;&nbsp;</p=
><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 1em 0;">At the heart of Web3 is the idea of <strong>consensus protocols</=
strong> and <strong>standards</strong> with money baked in. I think about i=
t like a series of open source <a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/=
eJxVkEFuxCAMRU8z7CbCJCRkwaKbXiMi4CZ0CETgdJTbl06kVpVss_iyP_9ZQ7ikfOo9FWI_Y6J=
zRx3xWQISYWZHwTx5p6EXqpXdyJzuHCipmC_TR0bcjA-a8oFsP-bgrSGf4muDcyHZqvsWrTTOKY=
7D2Cne9ij7AXowHK0Ffvmaw3mMFjV-YT5TRBb0SrSXW_t2E--1YqI5ZR-XphxzIWMfjU1bFfbaZ=
vflbkK404r3pznvLj0j81pwARyEhPp36Bto0mwAwmA_4dbxbRH_jrGsf12q_FjNhuEl1GxTfbcj=
ejonjGYO6K7YdNF7gZgWjJgrVTcZqswApBJK9iO0V8zKpYVBjUJ1rDq7VLfin-k3NXeISQ" sty=
le=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">APIs</a> that anyone can=
 use to build according to an agreed upon set of rules, that gain financial=
 value over time which is shared with everyone who contributes to the API.&=
nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 1em 0;">Instead of building siloed products, Web3 is built for <s=
trong>interoperability.</strong> This is a key concept, keep it in mind. De=
centralized Finance (&#8220;DeFi&#8221;), which, as the name implies, is at=
tempting to build a new financial system without central financial institut=
ions, is one of the most promising layers being built on Web3. A common ana=
logy for the way DeFi products are built is with &#8220;money legos.&#8221;=
 In a 2019 post, <em><a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMuOhC=
AQRb-m2bWxUGxcsJjN_IbhUSrTCAaL6fj3Q7eLSQgVUrncnGM14ZLyqfZ0EHtfE507qoivIyARZ=
