#1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">DeFi Prime</a> alone, each with their=
 own unique features and infrastructure. This means that if you picked any =
3 out of the roughly 200 listed tools, you&#8217;d have 1,313,400 different=
 combinations to choose from to build a new financial product.</em></p></bl=
ockquote><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 1em 0;">That mirrors one of the benefits of APIs that I wrote abo=
ut, namely:</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #67bdfc; margin:=
 1em 0;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1em;"><em><strong>There is also a competitive=
 advantage to be gained from how you leverage APIs to build your company an=
d product</strong>.&nbsp;</em></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1em;"><em>Using a bu=
nch of APIs that are really flexible, and figuring out good ways to connect=
 them, leads to a combinatorial explosion of potential workflows. API-first=
 companies turn software into like customizable building blocks.</em></p></=
blockquote><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 1em 0;">There&#8217;s a reason for the similarity. Web3, too, u=
ses APIs for software to talk to each other.&nbsp;</p><div class=3D"caption=
